bibdata.title: When we trigger a full dump in the alma sandbox(test environment), records from lib-sftp dont transfer in the bibdata-alma-staging box

comments.body:
@mzelesky deactivated again (for some reason it was active) the webhook-staging in the alma prod environment. 
- We were seeing the events in bibdata-staging because they were created from this webhook-staging in the alma prod - none of the staging events has files. 
- On Friday before deploying the ruby update in aws, I triggered an incremental publishing job in the alma-test (sandbox) environment. The files were transfered to lib-sftp through the webhook but the event failed to be created in bibdata-staging due to a ruby version error in the aws-webhook-listener. 
- On Friday evening I updated the webhook-listener on aws by doing a bundle install of all the gems in the webhook/src directory using ruby 2.7.5
- Sunday night I triggered a new incremental publishing job in the alma-sandbox.
- Monday 01-24-202, check if there is still a ruby version error in aws ; If there is no ruby version error in aws [webhook-staging listener](https://console.aws.amazon.com/cloudwatch/home?region=us-east-1#logsV2:log-groups/log-group/$252Faws$252Flambda$252Falma-webhook-monitor-staging-WebhookReceiver-za2o0tUQ0XNM/log-events/2022$252F01$252F21$252F$255B$2524LATEST$255D5f8f1770e3a54e22b05e7f6a8c6dd929/2022$252F01$252F21$252F$255B$2524LATEST$255D5f8f1770e3a54e22b05e7f6a8c6dd929$3Fstart$3D1642784463671$26refEventId$3D36635317742661832676676242934420454594344854306010693633)   then check if the event was created in https://bibdata-staging.princeton.edu/events and has files.

Monday 01-24-2022: the job I triggered last night created an event in bibdata but there were no files because there were no changes in the alma sandbox. @mzelesky submitted a job to alter 600 records. I triggered. This job finished. I triggered a new incremental publishing job. Will monitor if the files come in bibdata-staging and if they get indexed.
The bibdata event was created successfully. The dump files are in place. Files were not indexed :((

With ruby 2.5 in the webhook I can see on staging webhook the same datadog error https://console.aws.amazon.com/cloudwatch/home?region=us-east-1#logsV2:log-groups/log-group/$252Faws$252Flambda$252Falma-webhook-monitor-staging-WebhookReceiver-za2o0tUQ0XNM/log-events/2022$252F01$252F24$252F$255B$2524LATEST$255D94d3b3af61294794a3ff4aea6211761a

remaining to check if the records were indexed.
